# Juju Baby Tracker — Privacy Policy
_Last updated: TBD_

## 1. Introduction
Juju Baby Tracker (“the App”) is developed and operated by **Jason Phung** (“we,” “us,” or “our”). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect personal data when you use the App.

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 User Account Information
- Email address  
- Password (securely stored via Firebase Auth; we do not see or store your password)  
- Display name  
- Family photo (optional)

### 2.2 Baby Information
- Baby name  
- Birthdate  
- Gender  
- Length/weight measurements  
- Baby profile photo

### 2.3 Activity & Usage Data
- Feedings (amount, type, time)  
- Diapers  
- Sleep/Nap logs  
- Pump logs  
- Timestamps for all activities

## 3. Device Permissions
- Photo Library Access  
- Future: Push Notifications  
- No location data collected

## 4. How We Use Your Information
Used to operate the App, sync data, track activities, and maintain user accounts.  
We do not sell or rent data.

## 5. Advertising & Purchases
Uses **Google AdMob** to show ads.  
Optional one-time purchase removes all ads.

## 6. Data Storage & Security
Uses Firebase Authentication, Firestore, and Firebase Storage.
- All data encrypted in transit and at rest  
- No raw passwords are stored  
- TLS-secured connections

## 7. Data Sharing
No data shared except with Google Firebase and Google AdMob.  
We do not sell personal data.

## 8. Data Retention & Deletion
We retain data unless you request deletion.  
Email requests to **jujubabytracker@gmail.com**.

## 9. Children’s Privacy
Intended for adults; stores information about babies for parental use.  
Complies with COPPA.

## 10. International Users
Data may be stored/processed by Firebase in the United States or other regions.

## 11. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy periodically.

## 12. Contact
**Jason Phung**  
Massachusetts, USA  
Email: **jujubabytracker@gmail.com**
